18841 Our worthy acquaintance Mr Malachi Mulligan now appeared in the doorway
18842 as the students were finishing their apologue accompanied with a friend
18843 whom he had just rencountered, a young gentleman, his name Alec Bannon,
18844 who had late come to town, it being his intention to buy a colour or a
18845 cornetcy in the fencibles and list for the wars. Mr Mulligan was civil
18846 enough to express some relish of it all the more as it jumped with a
18847 project of his own for the cure of the very evil that had been touched
18848 on. Whereat he handed round to the company a set of pasteboard cards
18849 which he had had printed that day at Mr Quinnell's bearing a legend
18850 printed in fair italics: _Mr Malachi Mulligan. Fertiliser and Incubator.
18851 Lambay Island_. His project, as he went on to expound, was to withdraw
18852 from the round of idle pleasures such as form the chief business of sir
18853 Fopling Popinjay and sir Milksop Quidnunc in town and to devote himself
18854 to the noblest task for which our bodily organism has been framed. Well,
18855 let us hear of it, good my friend, said Mr Dixon. I make no doubt it
18856 smacks of wenching. Come, be seated, both. 'Tis as cheap sitting as
18857 standing. Mr Mulligan accepted of the invitation and, expatiating upon
18858 his design, told his hearers that he had been led into this thought by
18859 a consideration of the causes of sterility, both the inhibitory and the
18860 prohibitory, whether the inhibition in its turn were due to conjugal
18861 vexations or to a parsimony of the balance as well as whether the
18862 prohibition proceeded from defects congenital or from proclivities
18863 acquired. It grieved him plaguily, he said, to see the nuptial couch
18864 defrauded of its dearest pledges: and to reflect upon so many agreeable
18865 females with rich jointures, a prey to the vilest bonzes, who hide their
18866 flambeau under a bushel in an uncongenial cloister or lose their womanly
18867 bloom in the embraces of some unaccountable muskin when they might
18868 multiply the inlets of happiness, sacrificing the inestimable jewel of
18869 their sex when a hundred pretty fellows were at hand to caress, this, he
18870 assured them, made his heart weep. To curb this inconvenient (which
18871 he concluded due to a suppression of latent heat), having advised with
18872 certain counsellors of worth and inspected into this matter, he had
18873 resolved to purchase in fee simple for ever the freehold of Lambay
18874 island from its holder, lord Talbot de Malahide, a Tory gentleman of
18875 note much in favour with our ascendancy party. He proposed to set up
18876 there a national fertilising farm to be named _Omphalos_ with an obelisk
18877 hewn and erected after the fashion of Egypt and to offer his dutiful
18878 yeoman services for the fecundation of any female of what grade of life
18879 soever who should there direct to him with the desire of fulfilling the
18880 functions of her natural. Money was no object, he said, nor would he
18881 take a penny for his pains. The poorest kitchenwench no less than the
18882 opulent lady of fashion, if so be their constructions and their tempers
18883 were warm persuaders for their petitions, would find in him their man.
